{{Planes of existence}}
The '''soul(ful)''' or (to Indian neo-Theosophists) '''buddhic plane''' ([[hyperplane]] or [[spacetime|continuum]]/[[universe]], separately, or enclosing and interpenetrating grosser hyperplanes, respectively) or world (simply) in Theosophy is the world in which [[buddhi]], i.e. [[soul]], exists.

